  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# D²NN Optical MNIST: Interactive Explorer\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook allows you to run and explore differentiable optical neural networks (ONNs) for MNIST classification. It follows the progression from simple D²NN layers to translation-invariant ODCNN architectures.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🚀 Setup\n",
    "First, we clone the repository and install the necessary dependencies."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# REPLACE THIS WITH YOUR ACTUAL REPO URL\n",
    "REPO_URL = \"https://github.com/Lukasmax272/OpticalCNNproject/tree/main"\n",
    "\n",
    "!git clone {REPO_URL} project\n",
    "%cd project\n",
    "!pip install -r requirements.txt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Phase 1: Simple All-Optical D²NN\n",
    "Training a multi-layer (3-layer) diffractive network. This establishes the baseline accuracy for centered digits."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Run training for a 3-layer D2NN\n",
    "!python main.py --num-layers 3 --iters 2000"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Phase 2b: Motion Pooling (Translation Robust)\n",
    "Training a 4f correlator system with motion pooling to handle spatial shifts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!python main_phase2_motion_pool.py --grid 64 --iters 2000"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Benchmarking & Results\n",
    "Compare the architectures across a range of horizontal shifts to see how robust they are."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Evaluate the variants we just trained\n",
    "!python benchmark.py --variant \"Phase 1b\" --checkpoint learned_phase_mask_3l_64p.npy --num-layers 3\n",
    "!python benchmark.py --variant \"Phase 2b\" --checkpoint learned_phase_mask_4f_motion_64.npy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate the comparison plot\n",
    "!python benchmark.py --plot-all"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### View the Comparison Plot\n",
    "The plot below shows Accuracy vs. Pixel Shift. You will see the D²NN accuracy drop sharply with shifts, while the Motion Pooled system remains robust."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from IPython.display import Image, display\n",
    "display(Image(\"translation_invariance_mnist.png\"))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Visualizing Propagation\n",
    "Watch how a digit light-field propagates through the diffractive layers."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!python visualize_full_process.py\n",
    "display(Image(\"full_process_visualization.png\"))"
   ]
  }
